<section id="projects" class="projects-section">
  <h2>Projects</h2>
  <div class="project-list">

    <article class="project-card featured">
      <div class="badge">Evidence-based · Public repo · N=1 · Reproducible</div>
      <h3>ANS-Based Symptom Prediction in Post-Lyme Fatigue</h3>
      <p class="project-sub">N=1 Longitudinal Study · Consumer Wearable + AI Pipeline</p>
      <p>48-hour prediction of symptomatic exacerbations using autonomic wearable data. ANS status predicts severe symptom days with 81% sensitivity (AUC=0.656). Sleep metrics show zero predictive value — the signal lives in the autonomic nervous system. Pipeline runs entirely local via IO. Scripts and methodology public.</p>
      <p class="stack"><em>Python · scikit-learn · LangGraph · Polar Grit X2 · ChromaDB</em></p>
      <a href="https://github.com/kinetica-IA/polar-lyme-predictor" target="_blank" class="project-btn">View on GitHub →</a>
    </article>

    <article class="project-card">
      <div class="badge">Local · No cloud · Private · Clinical use case</div>
      <h3>IO · Local-First Clinical AI Agent</h3>
      <p class="project-sub">Autonomous Orchestration · RAG · ALMA Framework</p>
      <p>Autonomous AI agent running locally on Mac Mini M4. Orchestrates LLMs (qwen3:14b + Claude) via LangGraph, enriches context with RAG/ChromaDB, and applies ALMA — an ethical-cognitive framework for clinical reasoning. Demonstrated use case: autonomic monitoring and 48-hour symptom prediction in post-infectious fatigue.</p>
      <p class="stack"><em>LangGraph · Ollama · qwen3:14b · ChromaDB · MCP · Python</em></p>
    </article>

    <article class="project-card">
      <img src="/assets/IA-y-Empatia.png" alt="LLMs as Cognitive Mirrors" class="project-icon" />
      <h3>LLMs as Cognitive Mirrors: Clinical &amp; Ethical Dimensions</h3>
      <p>Research on the capabilities and limits of LLMs in clinical contexts — cognitive, ethical, and applied dimensions.</p>
      <p class="stack"><em>GPT-4 · LLaMA · Qualitative analysis</em></p>
    </article>

  </div>
</section>

<style>
